            "text": "Joule Per Kelvin (J/K) is a unit in the category of Entropy. It is also known as joules per kelvin, joule/kelvin. This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. Joule Per Kelvin (J/K) has a dimension of $ML^{2}T^{-2}Q^{-1}$ where $M$ is mass, $L$ is length, $T$ is time, and Q is temperature. This unit is the standard SI unit in this category.",
